265
00:16:25,910 --> 00:16:28,010
I bet reporters will flock to that like moths to a flame.

266
00:16:28,210 --> 00:16:29,950
You little punk...

267
00:16:30,150 --> 00:16:31,579
Are you threatening your own father?

268
00:16:31,580 --> 00:16:33,819
Yes, I am.

269
00:16:33,820 --> 00:16:36,420
I know you well enough to know that simply asking won't work.

270
00:16:39,220 --> 00:16:40,360
So what else could I do?

271
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:41,860
Should I go in?

272
00:16:42,790 --> 00:16:43,900
Should I open the door?

273
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:51,100
Fine.

274
00:16:51,670 --> 00:16:52,800
The suspension.

275
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:54,810
I'll make it go away.

276
00:16:55,310 --> 00:16:56,310
But...

277
00:16:57,640 --> 00:16:59,080
I have a condition of my own.

278
00:16:59,780 --> 00:17:01,909
If I'm going to be blackmailed by my own son,

279
00:17:01,910 --> 00:17:03,450
I need to get something out of this, too.

280
00:17:06,420 --> 00:17:07,550
Get tutored.

281
00:17:08,650 --> 00:17:10,420
At this rate,

282
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,490
you'll never get into a top university.

283
00:17:15,290 --> 00:17:16,390
Deal.

284
00:17:16,930 --> 00:17:19,360
Then let me go boxing. Just three times a week.

285
00:17:19,660 --> 00:17:21,300
You've got a lot of nerve.

286
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,500
- Twice.
- Three.

287
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:29,340
I can't go any lower. Anything less isn't a real workout.

288
00:17:30,010 --> 00:17:31,980
You punk. Seriously.

289
00:17:33,610 --> 00:17:36,980
Fine. But take your tutor seriously and get your grades up.

290
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:40,120
No slacking off. You hear me?

291
00:17:40,620 --> 00:17:41,620
Deal.

292
00:17:43,450 --> 00:17:44,619
Don't go back on your word.

293
00:17:44,620 --> 00:17:48,230
(Dongin Department Store)

294
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:56,369
Who does that kid take after to be so...

295
00:17:56,370 --> 00:17:58,900
darn bold?

296
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:01,570
What? What is it?

297
00:18:01,910 --> 00:18:03,369
Do you have something to say?

298
00:18:03,370 --> 00:18:04,480
No, sir.

299
00:18:40,710 --> 00:18:42,610
Giant.

300
00:18:43,850 --> 00:18:45,480
Giant.

301
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:52,219
Driver! Watch where you're going!

302
00:18:52,220 --> 00:18:54,089
I almost fell over!

303
00:18:54,090 --> 00:18:57,660
- I'm sorry. A car cut me off.
- Be careful, please.

304
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,730
I found it! Giant!

305
00:19:04,740 --> 00:19:05,740
Wait.

306
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:08,640
Are you hurt?

307
00:19:08,940 --> 00:19:11,910
I'm so sorry.

308
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:17,080
(Giant)

309
00:19:29,730 --> 00:19:31,260
Koh Yeong Rye. Where are you going?

310
00:19:31,460 --> 00:19:33,630
- Hey. Aren't you going to eat?
- No, I'm not eating!

311
00:19:34,070 --> 00:19:35,530
Hey. Where are you off to?

312
00:19:42,170 --> 00:19:43,269
Enjoy your meal!

313
00:19:43,270 --> 00:19:44,580
You too. Dig in.

314
00:19:45,980 --> 00:19:47,849
Where did Yeong Rye go? How come you're alone?

315
00:19:47,850 --> 00:19:49,550
I don't know. She said she wasn't hungry.

316
00:19:50,010 --> 00:19:51,449
She rushed off somewhere.

317
00:19:51,450 --> 00:19:53,219
What's up with that glutton?

318
00:19:53,220 --> 00:19:55,749
That girl would never skip a meal unless she was carsick.

319
00:19:55,750 --> 00:19:58,590
Gosh. Even if she's exhausted, she'll never miss a meal.

320
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:01,190
Pigs must be flying.

321
00:20:01,790 --> 00:20:04,860
What is with me these days, seriously?

322
00:20:05,430 --> 00:20:07,469
I mean, their senior is sitting right here.

323
00:20:07,470 --> 00:20:10,570
And not one of them thinks to get me some water.

324
00:20:11,970 --> 00:20:15,540
Back in my day, we really hustled. Right?

325
00:20:17,980 --> 00:20:20,749
Hey! Are you all deaf?

326
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:23,149
She just said she's thirsty!

327
00:20:23,150 --> 00:20:24,679
I'll run and get it for you.

328
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:25,720
No, it's fine.

329
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:27,590
I'll do it myself.

330
00:20:43,500 --> 00:20:45,700
Here you are, my senior.

331
00:20:58,720 --> 00:20:59,850
Driver Kim.

332
00:20:59,950 --> 00:21:01,120
Where?

333
00:21:01,490 --> 00:21:02,920
Ms. Kim. Did you get a perm?

334
00:21:03,650 --> 00:21:04,760
It looks great.

335
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:07,490
Enjoy your meal.

336
00:21:08,330 --> 00:21:10,830
There's Ms. Choi and Ho Suk...

337
00:21:11,100 --> 00:21:12,760
Ho Suk. You're looking prettier than ever.

338
00:21:13,330 --> 00:21:14,499
Did you get a boyfriend or something?

339
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:16,070
Come on now.

340
00:21:16,300 --> 00:21:19,369
Gosh. There's nothing like that at all.

341
00:21:19,370 --> 00:21:21,369
I bet there's a whole lot more to the story.

342
00:21:21,370 --> 00:21:23,409
Something's different about her, but what?

343
00:21:23,410 --> 00:21:24,780
Driver Kim.

344
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:26,709
There's a seat over here.

345
00:21:26,710 --> 00:21:29,009
Ms. Kwon. It's been a while. Did you save this seat for me?

346
00:21:29,010 --> 00:21:30,150
- Yes, sir.
- Thank you.

347
00:21:34,690 --> 00:21:35,790
Is she a new hire?

348
00:21:39,590 --> 00:21:40,690
Yes, she is.

349
00:21:40,790 --> 00:21:43,729
Please wait just a moment. I'll go get you some water.

350
00:21:43,730 --> 00:21:45,660
I appreciate it, Ms. Kwon. Thank you.

351
00:21:46,060 --> 00:21:47,730
Ok Hui. Go on and eat. Sit down.

352
00:21:49,970 --> 00:21:53,099
But Ok Hui, you already had a perm, didn't you?

353
00:21:53,100 --> 00:21:54,439
That's right. My curls are just...

354
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:55,909
- Oh, my!
- That's cold!

355
00:21:55,910 --> 00:21:58,539
Oh, my gosh. I'm sorry!

356
00:21:58,540 --> 00:22:01,649
I'm really not so clumsy.

357
00:22:01,650 --> 00:22:02,949
It's okay. Oh, that's cold.

358
00:22:02,950 --> 00:22:05,120
Gosh. I'm so sorry, Driver Kim.

359
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:08,590
I drink my water warm, but she brought me cold water.

360
00:22:08,890 --> 00:22:11,459
His clothes are soaked. What a mess.

361
00:22:11,460 --> 00:22:13,890
It's all right, Ms. Kwon. It's okay.

362
00:22:18,860 --> 00:22:22,400
(Giant Night Club)

363
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:25,700
(Giant, 10th Anniversary, May 21, 1982)

364
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:29,540
He didn't seem like the type to hang out here.

365
00:22:30,910 --> 00:22:32,910
(Giant)

366
00:22:35,810 --> 00:22:37,420
- Come in, please.
- Okay.

367
00:22:42,050 --> 00:22:45,060
(Giant Night Club)

368
00:22:55,370 --> 00:22:57,699
It's a raid! The cops are here!

369
00:22:57,700 --> 00:22:59,269
You. Hurry and run that way.

370
00:22:59,270 --> 00:23:00,670
And you! Run this way!

371
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:08,179
It's not me!

372
00:23:08,180 --> 00:23:10,009
- I'm not underage!
- Get over here. Come on.

373
00:23:10,010 --> 00:23:11,280
Go get them!

374
00:23:11,950 --> 00:23:13,680
(Giant Night Club)

375
00:23:14,490 --> 00:23:15,620
Why did you run away?

376
00:23:19,420 --> 00:23:20,420
Stand up properly.

377
00:23:20,520 --> 00:23:23,159
So, if you had your ID on you, why did you run away?

378
00:23:23,160 --> 00:23:24,500
Well, it's just...

379
00:23:24,900 --> 00:23:26,200
I was just so startled.

380
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:29,000
When you started chasing me, I ran without thinking.

381
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:30,570
Gosh. Some people...

382
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:37,340
Here you go.

383
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:39,080
Thank you.

384
00:23:41,050 --> 00:23:42,810
Hey! Can't you stand up straight?

385
00:23:43,210 --> 00:23:45,150
Just a bunch of kids, still wet behind the ears.

386
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:46,920
Hurry up. Let's go!

387
00:24:02,830 --> 00:24:03,930
Koh Yeong Rye?

388
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:07,270
Koh Yeong Rye!

389
00:24:08,010 --> 00:24:10,269
Where have you been?

390
00:24:10,270 --> 00:24:11,580
Do you have any idea what time it is?

391
00:24:14,180 --> 00:24:15,180
Hey.

392
00:24:15,380 --> 00:24:17,349
Don't tell me you were at that Giant place again...

393
00:24:17,350 --> 00:24:18,350
Seo Jong Hee.

394
00:24:18,351 --> 00:24:20,420
(Cheongah Bus)

395
00:24:21,620 --> 00:24:23,350
I need you to slap me.

396
00:24:24,120 --> 00:24:25,120
What?

397
00:24:25,320 --> 00:24:26,660
I need to snap out of it.

398
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:30,230
Go on. Do it. And make it hard.

399
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:32,560
Seriously?

400
00:24:32,760 --> 00:24:34,000
Yes, I'm serious.

401
00:24:34,870 --> 00:24:36,430
I promise I won't hold it against you.

402
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,500
Just do it.

403
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:46,409
Wait.

404
00:24:46,410 --> 00:24:48,249
Wait.

405
00:24:48,250 --> 00:24:49,410
Don't hit me.

406
00:24:50,610 --> 00:24:53,280
Just pinch me. That's better.

407
00:24:57,760 --> 00:24:59,220
Where have you been?

408
00:25:00,160 --> 00:25:03,190
So did you end up meeting Giant or not?

409
00:25:05,830 --> 00:25:07,130
From now on,

410
00:25:08,100 --> 00:25:09,630
I'm going to forget all about Giant.

411
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:11,900
And...

412
00:25:13,670 --> 00:25:15,040
I'm going to apply for that instead.

413
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:23,610
(Recruiting Applicants for Night School)

414
00:25:34,330 --> 00:25:35,560
If I enrol in this,

415
00:25:36,630 --> 00:25:38,600
you're sure the company will give me time off for this, right?

416
00:25:39,100 --> 00:25:40,100
Yes.

417
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:42,230
I checked. I'm sure.

418
00:25:43,100 --> 00:25:45,100
But studying and I just don't mix.

419
00:25:46,670 --> 00:25:49,670
And there's one more important thing.

420
00:25:50,170 --> 00:25:52,740
Apparently, you need a diploma to be in the Miss Korea pageant.

421
00:26:05,620 --> 00:26:07,090
Gosh. They're all so pretty.

422
00:26:07,390 --> 00:26:08,830
We're pretty too.

423
00:26:09,130 --> 00:26:10,860
Right. You mean you.

424
00:26:11,860 --> 00:26:13,160
You're pretty too.

425
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:16,200
Although I am a bit prettier, of course.

426
00:26:18,670 --> 00:26:19,670
Anyway...

427
00:26:20,170 --> 00:26:21,509
Are you going to completely forget about Giant...

428
00:26:21,510 --> 00:26:24,069
Hey. Why would you bring him up again?

429
00:26:24,070 --> 00:26:26,079
Don't bring up Giant anymore.

430
00:26:26,080 --> 00:26:27,480
Just don't.

431
00:26:27,980 --> 00:26:30,080
Giant.

432
00:26:33,980 --> 00:26:36,790
Now, I'm stuck having to go to school.

433
00:26:37,090 --> 00:26:38,119
Since we have to go anyway,

434
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:39,990
night school kids should get uniforms.

435
00:26:40,760 --> 00:26:42,630
Day students and night students. Isn't this blatant discrimination?

436
00:26:43,730 --> 00:26:45,429
Uniforms cost money, you know.

437
00:26:45,430 --> 00:26:47,600
I guess since we're basically going for free.

438
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,500
That's just sad.

439
00:26:51,570 --> 00:26:53,240
All this sadness is making me hungry.

440
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:54,710
Let's go get something to eat.

441
00:26:55,770 --> 00:26:56,770
Food?

442
00:26:58,410 --> 00:27:00,810
I know an amazing place for soybean paste stew.

443
00:27:01,110 --> 00:27:02,210
Do you want to go?

444
00:27:02,610 --> 00:27:03,650
Let's go.

445
00:27:03,950 --> 00:27:05,320
- Let's go.
- Go!

446
00:27:08,750 --> 00:27:09,850
This is the place.

447
00:27:12,090 --> 00:27:14,590
Koh Yeong Bae. Koh Yeong Mi.

448
00:27:14,790 --> 00:27:16,860
- Yeong Rye!
- Yeong Rye!

449
00:27:17,060 --> 00:27:18,200
How have you two been?

450
00:27:24,470 --> 00:27:26,440
Say hello. This is my friend.

451
00:27:26,640 --> 00:27:28,070
Hello.

452
00:27:29,710 --> 00:27:30,740
Go on. Say hello.

453
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:32,510
Hello.

454
00:27:33,140 --> 00:27:34,510
Hi, little ones.

455
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:37,780
I'm your sister's friend,

456
00:27:37,980 --> 00:27:39,120
Seo Jong Hee.

457
00:27:46,490 --> 00:27:47,520
Here. I got you something!

458
00:27:49,730 --> 00:27:50,790
Pastries!

459
00:27:51,100 --> 00:27:52,760
Gosh. Pastries!

460
00:27:53,100 --> 00:27:54,300
Pastries!

461
00:27:57,770 --> 00:27:59,340
Yeong Mi. Here, have some water.

462
00:28:01,570 --> 00:28:02,810
You too, Yeong Bae.

463
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:08,280
Koh Yeong Mi.

464
00:28:08,750 --> 00:28:10,649
Do you know what 4 divided by 4 is?

465
00:28:10,650 --> 00:28:11,949
No. What's that?

466
00:28:11,950 --> 00:28:14,649
It's 1. If there are 4 people and 4 pastries,

467
00:28:14,650 --> 00:28:16,790
it means each person gets to eat one.

468
00:28:18,420 --> 00:28:20,420
I guess being a stickler for the numbers runs in the family.

469
00:28:20,960 --> 00:28:21,960
But...

470
00:28:22,760 --> 00:28:24,530
Even in math, there's a little wiggle room.

471
00:28:27,030 --> 00:28:28,130
Here you go.

472
00:28:29,830 --> 00:28:31,170
Today's your lucky day.

473
00:28:36,010 --> 00:28:37,010
Okay.

474
00:28:37,210 --> 00:28:38,540
Thank you.

475
00:28:39,210 --> 00:28:40,440
Eat slowly.

476
00:28:43,050 --> 00:28:44,150
Should I give some to Yeong Bae too?

477
00:28:50,120 --> 00:28:52,890
- Mom.
- Good grief. You're always here.

478
00:28:53,390 --> 00:28:54,959
I told you to sleep in on your day off.

479
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,259
Why do you keep coming over?

480
00:28:56,260 --> 00:28:57,530
Goodness. You are so stubborn.

481
00:28:58,700 --> 00:29:00,660
My mom's got such a sharp tongue.

482
00:29:00,860 --> 00:29:02,200
Even though she's happy to see me.

483
00:29:02,300 --> 00:29:03,770
Happy? As if.

484
00:29:04,570 --> 00:29:06,370
Why would I be happy about another mouth to feed?

485
00:29:07,740 --> 00:29:09,010
And who's this?

486
00:29:09,570 --> 00:29:11,179
Hello, I'm...

487
00:29:11,180 --> 00:29:13,980
I'm Yeong Rye's roommate. My name is Seo Jong Hee.

488
00:29:14,510 --> 00:29:15,610
Is that right?

489
00:29:16,080 --> 00:29:17,980
Well, now, look at you.

490
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:19,980
Aren't you a pretty one?

491
00:29:21,020 --> 00:29:22,990
Since you're here, you might as well stay for a bite.

492
00:29:23,390 --> 00:29:25,290
Good thing you don't look like a big eater.

493
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:26,920
Give it.

494
00:29:28,490 --> 00:29:30,090
That's just her way of saying she's glad you're here.

495
00:29:30,360 --> 00:29:31,729
That's just how my mom is.

496
00:29:31,730 --> 00:29:33,230
I got the message, loud and clear.

497
00:29:34,570 --> 00:29:37,199
Mom. Is Yeong Sik coming home late today?

498
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:39,440
I feel like I haven't seen him in ages.

499
00:29:45,540 --> 00:29:46,810
Hi, brother!

500
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:49,879
Hyeon. Hi.

501
00:29:49,880 --> 00:29:50,950
Hey.

502
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:55,419
Even Mr. Popular gets tired, I see.

503
00:29:55,420 --> 00:29:56,919
Tired? Not at all.

504
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:59,259
If my smile can bring happiness to even one person...

505
00:29:59,260 --> 00:30:01,459
Then, according to the Constitution of Korea, Article ten.

506
00:30:01,460 --> 00:30:04,289
"All citizens have the right to pursue happiness."

507
00:30:04,290 --> 00:30:05,700
You'll find an excuse for anything, won't you?

508
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:07,969
Are you just getting here now? I didn't see you in class.

509
00:30:07,970 --> 00:30:09,330
No, I'm on my way out.

510
00:30:09,530 --> 00:30:10,670
I decided to skip class.

511
00:30:10,870 --> 00:30:14,100
The weather was too nice, so I was photosynthesising.

512
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:17,770
Hey. But why are you leaving already?

513
00:30:18,980 --> 00:30:20,739
Right. Today's the day, isn't it?

514
00:30:20,740 --> 00:30:22,450
That tutoring gig. Your secret side hustle.

515
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:24,779
Thanks for setting me up.

516
00:30:24,780 --> 00:30:26,120
I'll treat you when I get my first paycheck.

517
00:30:26,220 --> 00:30:29,290
Don't worry. Think of all the meals I eat at your place.

518
00:30:29,750 --> 00:30:31,119
You know that's in my neighbourhood, right?

519
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:33,160
I'll be around, so when you're done...

520
00:30:34,320 --> 00:30:35,330
Why?

521
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:38,060
Again?

522
00:30:39,060 --> 00:30:40,629
The Constitution of Korea, Article 17.

523
00:30:40,630 --> 00:30:43,900
"All citizens have the right to privacy and freedom from intrusion."

524
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:46,340
So call me. I'm not eating dinner until you do.

525
00:31:49,500 --> 00:31:52,099
Please, take it. No need to make a fuss.

526
00:31:52,100 --> 00:31:53,500
Yes, ma'am.

527
00:31:54,740 --> 00:31:57,409
The wife of the Hwashin Electronics chairman told me...

528
00:31:57,410 --> 00:32:00,240
that you were a top student at Minguk University.

529
00:32:00,540 --> 00:32:02,849
I was expecting you to look geeky,

530
00:32:02,850 --> 00:32:04,450
but you're quite handsome.

531
00:32:04,650 --> 00:32:05,849
Has anyone ever...

532
00:32:05,850 --> 00:32:08,790
told you that you look like Clark Gable?

533
00:32:08,990 --> 00:32:12,059
You know, the actor from "Gone with the Wind?"

534
00:32:12,060 --> 00:32:16,290
I think there's a resemblance in your eyes and your jawline.

535
00:32:16,490 --> 00:32:17,589
- Do you think so?
- Yes.

