796
00:46:18,170 --> 00:46:21,600
You bet. If you start to nod off, I'll be there to wake you up.

797
00:46:22,070 --> 00:46:23,509
You're one scary woman.

798
00:46:23,510 --> 00:46:26,410
You're a sly fox disguised as a teddy bear.

799
00:46:27,780 --> 00:46:29,510
Okay, fine.

800
00:46:29,710 --> 00:46:30,780
Since...

801
00:46:31,080 --> 00:46:34,120
Since you were so thoughtful, I'll carry it with me always.

802
00:46:34,420 --> 00:46:36,720
I can't promise I'll actually study with it, though.

803
00:46:37,920 --> 00:46:39,220
- Let's go.
- Okay.

804
00:46:54,070 --> 00:46:55,670
- What is it?
- Look at this.

805
00:46:56,710 --> 00:46:58,569
(Good luck to whoever is studying here!)

806
00:46:58,570 --> 00:46:59,809
That's cute.

807
00:46:59,810 --> 00:47:02,510
That's adorable. I should write back.

808
00:47:21,900 --> 00:47:24,770
Excuse me. One second. I think my MyMy is at my desk.

809
00:47:24,970 --> 00:47:26,900
It's here. Thank goodness.

810
00:47:28,840 --> 00:47:31,840
Excuse me. You're from Bus 100, right?

811
00:47:32,340 --> 00:47:35,040
You're the one who gave me a ride when I was about to be late.

812
00:47:35,580 --> 00:47:36,710
Oh, right!

813
00:47:36,910 --> 00:47:38,149
You're that student.

814
00:47:38,150 --> 00:47:40,519
That's me. I can't believe you're here...

815
00:47:40,520 --> 00:47:42,789
- It's so good to see you!
- It's so good to see you too!

816
00:47:42,790 --> 00:47:44,919
This is so crazy. What are the odds...

817
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:45,960
Hello?

818
00:47:46,620 --> 00:47:48,459
I was there with her that day, you know?

819
00:47:48,460 --> 00:47:49,690
Get over here, then.

820
00:47:50,990 --> 00:47:52,430
This is so wild.

821
00:47:56,800 --> 00:47:58,199
- Mom.
- Yes?

822
00:47:58,200 --> 00:48:00,769
Why are you closing up so early today?

823
00:48:00,770 --> 00:48:02,940
Well, it's nice to have a day like this once in a while.

824
00:48:04,110 --> 00:48:06,480
We sold out of all the sugar we brought.

825
00:48:06,580 --> 00:48:09,350
And we were packed with customers for the horse rides all day long.

826
00:48:09,550 --> 00:48:10,550
Oh, gosh.

827
00:48:10,551 --> 00:48:13,879
If every day were like today, we would be rich in no time.

828
00:48:13,880 --> 00:48:15,819
Really? Are we rich now, Mom?

829
00:48:15,820 --> 00:48:18,150
Of course! To us, this is a fortune.

830
00:48:21,560 --> 00:48:23,989
Yeong Bae. Yeong Mi. Come here for a second.

831
00:48:23,990 --> 00:48:24,990
Okay!

832
00:48:26,860 --> 00:48:27,960
Here you go.

833
00:48:28,160 --> 00:48:30,369
Here. Go buy yourselves some ice pops.

834
00:48:30,370 --> 00:48:31,799
Gosh. Ice pops!

835
00:48:31,800 --> 00:48:33,100
Let's go, Yeong Mi!

836
00:48:35,300 --> 00:48:36,870
Honestly.

837
00:48:37,070 --> 00:48:38,640
It's the little things that make them so happy.

838
00:48:44,210 --> 00:48:45,410
Oh, my goodness!

839
00:48:51,390 --> 00:48:52,460
Oh, no!

840
00:49:00,560 --> 00:49:01,560
Oh, no.

841
00:49:05,940 --> 00:49:07,270
Oh, goodness.

842
00:49:11,070 --> 00:49:12,609
Koh Yeong Rye. Hurry home!

843
00:49:12,610 --> 00:49:14,680
Your mom was in an accident and got hurt!

844
00:49:25,220 --> 00:49:26,220
Mom!

845
00:49:27,920 --> 00:49:30,390
Mom, are you okay? Are you all right?

846
00:49:30,790 --> 00:49:32,800
What's all the fuss?

847
00:49:33,130 --> 00:49:36,399
I'm not dead. Don't be so dramatic.

848
00:49:36,400 --> 00:49:37,830
What happened?

849
00:49:38,530 --> 00:49:40,440
How did this happen?

850
00:49:40,900 --> 00:49:43,510
She was pulling her cart up a hill, and she fell.

851
00:49:43,710 --> 00:49:45,570
She cut up her knees and arms a bit.

852
00:49:45,880 --> 00:49:48,780
And I told her to go to the hospital in case of internal injuries,

853
00:49:49,650 --> 00:49:51,209
but she's being stubborn, as usual.

854
00:49:51,210 --> 00:49:54,550
Mom, come on. You're really worrying me.

855
00:49:54,980 --> 00:49:56,389
We need to get you to a hospital.

856
00:49:56,390 --> 00:49:58,889
A hospital? Don't be ridiculous.

857
00:49:58,890 --> 00:50:01,160
Cut the nonsense.

858
00:50:01,990 --> 00:50:03,730
The hospital is the least of my worries.

859
00:50:04,730 --> 00:50:08,400
That cart. What am I going to do about the cart?

860
00:50:09,330 --> 00:50:11,129
I had to go to the head of my savings club...

861
00:50:11,130 --> 00:50:15,100
and beg to get the first payout so I could finally buy it.

862
00:50:16,170 --> 00:50:18,939
I still have a year of payments, and now I've gone and destroyed it.

863
00:50:18,940 --> 00:50:21,139
What am I going to do? Goodness.

864
00:50:21,140 --> 00:50:23,609
- Mom.
- Mom.

865
00:50:23,610 --> 00:50:25,710
I guess you can't escape your fate.

866
00:50:26,180 --> 00:50:30,020
I just had to open my big mouth and say we were okay. I jinxed it.

867
00:50:30,620 --> 00:50:33,820
That's how I feed my family of five. What am I going to do?

868
00:50:37,260 --> 00:50:41,160
My poor kids. What's going to happen to them?

869
00:50:43,530 --> 00:50:47,340
Mom.

870
00:51:07,190 --> 00:51:08,520
(Bus)

871
00:51:21,470 --> 00:51:23,010
One at a time, please!

872
00:51:26,710 --> 00:51:28,040
Hurry on up.

873
00:51:30,050 --> 00:51:31,250
All clear!

874
00:52:14,190 --> 00:52:15,220
Manager,

875
00:52:15,860 --> 00:52:17,830
can't you make just one exception?

876
00:52:17,930 --> 00:52:19,299
Please, sir. Just this once.

877
00:52:19,300 --> 00:52:21,730
I'm in a really desperate spot.

878
00:52:22,430 --> 00:52:24,570
Yeong Rye. Are you that desperate?

879
00:52:25,300 --> 00:52:26,300
Yes.

880
00:52:26,500 --> 00:52:28,799
Well, I've got bigger problems. All right?

881
00:52:28,800 --> 00:52:32,270
Corporate is breathing down my neck about our deposit numbers.

882
00:52:32,470 --> 00:52:34,310
This job is going to be the death of me.

883
00:52:34,410 --> 00:52:35,949
And I'd like to live a long life.

884
00:52:35,950 --> 00:52:37,149
Manager.

885
00:52:37,150 --> 00:52:40,220
Forget it. Every single one of you has some sob story.

886
00:52:40,420 --> 00:52:42,249
Someone's parents are on death's door.

887
00:52:42,250 --> 00:52:44,219
For another, their house is flooded and destroyed every other day.

888
00:52:44,220 --> 00:52:46,789
I mean, if I hear this sob story and that sob story,

889
00:52:46,790 --> 00:52:48,459
how is the company supposed to stay in business?

890
00:52:48,460 --> 00:52:49,560
Are we running a charity here?

891
00:52:49,660 --> 00:52:51,229
Do you think money just grows on trees?

892
00:52:51,230 --> 00:52:53,159
That we can just pluck it whenever we want?

893
00:52:53,160 --> 00:52:54,160
Then...

894
00:52:54,900 --> 00:52:56,669
If you can't give me a two-month advance...

895
00:52:56,670 --> 00:52:58,429
- How about just one month's?
- Hey.

896
00:52:58,430 --> 00:53:00,440
What if you just take the advance and run off?

897
00:53:00,640 --> 00:53:02,339
How am I supposed to cover that?

898
00:53:02,340 --> 00:53:04,169
You're really making this difficult for me.

899
00:53:04,170 --> 00:53:05,170
For goodness' sake.

900
00:53:05,171 --> 00:53:07,239
You know I'm not that kind of person.

901
00:53:07,240 --> 00:53:09,109
Sir, I would never just run off.

902
00:53:09,110 --> 00:53:10,779
I promise on my life. I really mean it.

903
00:53:10,780 --> 00:53:11,880
"Promise?"

904
00:53:12,080 --> 00:53:14,979
You know what I don't believe in? Promises. You hear me?

905
00:53:14,980 --> 00:53:16,449
And I trust people even less.

906
00:53:16,450 --> 00:53:17,689
Absolutely not. Now get out.

907
00:53:17,690 --> 00:53:19,189
Manager, please.

908
00:53:19,190 --> 00:53:21,759
I just have nowhere else to turn.

909
00:53:21,760 --> 00:53:23,759
Quiet! Get out! Go on. Get back to work.

910
00:53:23,760 --> 00:53:25,490
Get out!

911
00:53:46,650 --> 00:53:47,980
What brings you here?

912
00:53:49,520 --> 00:53:51,320
I doubt you came just to check on me.

913
00:53:51,950 --> 00:53:53,290
Uncle.

914
00:53:54,060 --> 00:53:56,330
The money you borrowed from my dad...

915
00:53:57,160 --> 00:53:58,960
Could you please pay it back?

916
00:53:59,160 --> 00:54:00,160
What?

917
00:54:01,660 --> 00:54:03,130
You people in this family...

918
00:54:03,730 --> 00:54:05,770
are always harping on about that money.

919
00:54:06,640 --> 00:54:08,139
Your mother came here and made a scene...

920
00:54:08,140 --> 00:54:10,310
when your brother started college.

921
00:54:10,510 --> 00:54:13,780
I already paid that money back. How many times must I tell you?

922
00:54:17,180 --> 00:54:18,810
But you didn't.

923
00:54:19,010 --> 00:54:20,420
We know everything.

924
00:54:25,490 --> 00:54:26,620
Then...

925
00:54:28,090 --> 00:54:29,490
Lend me some money, then.

926
00:54:29,690 --> 00:54:31,390
I promise I'll pay you back.

927
00:54:31,890 --> 00:54:35,830
My mom was in an accident, and her cart was destroyed.

928
00:54:36,030 --> 00:54:37,569
She's hurt, too.

929
00:54:37,570 --> 00:54:39,540
But she's refusing to even go to the hospital.

930
00:54:40,070 --> 00:54:41,470
I'll pay you back.

931
00:54:41,670 --> 00:54:44,540
I promise I'll find a way to pay you back someday.

932
00:54:45,840 --> 00:54:47,610
Business has been slow for us lately.

933
00:54:48,210 --> 00:54:49,750
We're completely tapped out...

934
00:54:49,950 --> 00:54:51,080
of money.

935
00:54:51,580 --> 00:54:53,879
And frankly...

936
00:54:53,880 --> 00:54:57,420
Your mother is the one who cut us off in the first place.

937
00:54:57,950 --> 00:55:00,889
She ghosts us on the holidays without so much as a phone call.

938
00:55:00,890 --> 00:55:04,390
But you only show up when you need money.

939
00:55:12,740 --> 00:55:14,240
Here. Take this for bus fare.

940
00:59:35,060 --> 00:59:37,330
Gosh. What on earth happened?

941
00:59:37,700 --> 00:59:39,130
I'm fine, really.

942
00:59:39,800 --> 00:59:41,370
You silly goose.

943
00:59:41,870 --> 00:59:44,139
If it's raining, you could at least buy a cheap umbrella.

944
00:59:44,140 --> 00:59:46,909
What are you doing, wandering around in the rain?

945
00:59:46,910 --> 00:59:48,510
You're going to catch a cold.

946
00:59:49,080 --> 00:59:50,180
Oh, no.

947
00:59:50,550 --> 00:59:53,379
And what on earth happened to your nails?

948
00:59:53,380 --> 00:59:54,420
What's this here?

949
00:59:57,050 --> 00:59:59,150
I'm a total wreck, aren't I?

950
01:00:00,020 --> 01:00:03,360
Just hold still. I'll go find a bandage for that.

951
01:00:04,660 --> 01:00:07,360
It's always one thing after another with you, Koh Yeong Rye.

952
01:00:07,830 --> 01:00:09,229
The housemother is already complaining...

953
01:00:09,230 --> 01:00:10,970
that our room's deposits are always short.

954
01:00:11,730 --> 01:00:13,939
So don't you dare get sick and miss work.

955
01:00:13,940 --> 01:00:15,370
You'll be dead meat.

956
01:00:15,570 --> 01:00:17,070
The rest of you, get to bed!

957
01:00:17,770 --> 01:00:20,080
Listen to Hae Ja, girls.

958
01:00:22,540 --> 01:00:24,109
How on earth did you get so hurt?

959
01:00:24,110 --> 01:00:25,250
I'm okay.

960
01:00:52,770 --> 01:00:54,510
If all those stars were money,

961
01:00:57,380 --> 01:00:58,910
I'd stay up all night,

962
01:01:00,250 --> 01:01:01,720
whatever it takes,

963
01:01:03,890 --> 01:01:05,150
and I'd pick them all,

964
01:01:07,590 --> 01:01:09,120
every last one.

965
01:01:37,690 --> 01:01:38,820
What are you up to?

966
01:01:39,020 --> 01:01:40,360
Come on in.

967
01:01:43,690 --> 01:01:45,130
What are you doing, Ms. Koh?

968
01:01:45,860 --> 01:01:47,129
It's not like you're exercising under the moonlight.

969
01:01:47,130 --> 01:01:48,260
Why the cleaning?

970
01:01:49,830 --> 01:01:52,169
I probably won't want to do it at dawn tomorrow,

971
01:01:52,170 --> 01:01:53,200
so I'm doing it now.

972
01:01:53,300 --> 01:01:54,300
Right.

973
01:01:55,170 --> 01:01:57,470
Cleaning at 4 am is no joke.

974
01:01:58,970 --> 01:02:01,640
I'm still going to wait until tomorrow, though.

975
01:02:18,690 --> 01:02:21,800
You're upset about your mom's accident, aren't you?

976
01:02:28,540 --> 01:02:30,510
I guess you don't know I have superpowers.

977
01:02:32,140 --> 01:02:33,380
The truth is...

978
01:02:34,240 --> 01:02:36,680
I'm an alien from a star called Andromeda.

979
01:02:38,250 --> 01:02:39,480
And that's why...

980
01:02:39,680 --> 01:02:42,780
I can see right through what humans are thinking.

981
01:02:44,320 --> 01:02:45,890
- Really?
- Yes.

982
01:02:47,720 --> 01:02:49,620
Or so I'd like to say, but...

983
01:02:50,660 --> 01:02:52,530
I just don't have the energy for it today.

984
01:02:56,100 --> 01:02:57,670
Then how did you know?

985
01:02:59,430 --> 01:03:01,570
Just a lucky guess.

986
01:03:15,920 --> 01:03:17,020
Here.

987
01:03:18,920 --> 01:03:21,120
What's this for?

988
01:03:21,220 --> 01:03:22,320
It's a gift.

989
01:03:23,230 --> 01:03:24,930
You gave me one, too.

990
01:03:26,260 --> 01:03:27,630
It might not look like much,

991
01:03:28,430 --> 01:03:30,930
but he's a pretty hefty guy.

992
01:03:51,420 --> 01:03:52,890
I can't...

993
01:03:53,290 --> 01:03:55,490
Use this to get your mom a new cart.

994
01:03:56,290 --> 01:03:57,730
I'm not just giving it to you, though.

995
01:03:57,830 --> 01:03:59,060
It's a loan.

996
01:04:00,160 --> 01:04:03,470
You can pay me when you're a teacher and you get your first paycheck.

997
01:04:04,070 --> 01:04:05,499
And I won't charge you interest.

998
01:04:05,500 --> 01:04:07,239
No, I can't take this.

999
01:04:07,240 --> 01:04:09,299
How can I possibly take this much money from you?

1000
01:04:09,300 --> 01:04:10,410
Just take it.

1001
01:04:12,010 --> 01:04:13,910
This is what this money is for.

1002
01:04:14,440 --> 01:04:15,939
End of discussion.

1003
01:04:15,940 --> 01:04:17,479
Jong Hee, but really...

1004
01:04:17,480 --> 01:04:18,980
Come on. Just take it.

1005
01:04:20,820 --> 01:04:23,720
Fine. Then, as a bonus, I'm putting one favour in the bank.

1006
01:04:24,490 --> 01:04:26,720
And you have to grant it, no matter what. Okay?

1007
01:04:29,590 --> 01:04:32,760
But still, I can't take it.

1008
01:04:33,460 --> 01:04:34,700
Take it.

1009
01:04:34,800 --> 01:04:36,730
I'll be hurt if you don't.

1010
01:04:41,700 --> 01:04:43,040
If it makes you feel better,

1011
01:04:45,210 --> 01:04:47,040
then you can pay me back a certain amount each month.

1012
01:04:59,990 --> 01:05:00,990
Hey.

1013
01:05:01,390 --> 01:05:02,490
What is it?

1014
01:05:03,360 --> 01:05:05,030
Koh Yeong Rye. Are you crying?

1015
01:05:05,490 --> 01:05:07,430
I'm not crying. It's just the rain.

1016
01:05:08,060 --> 01:05:09,800
The rain stopped a while ago.

1017
01:05:11,400 --> 01:05:13,100
Gosh. Koh Yeong Rye.

1018
01:05:13,900 --> 01:05:16,100
You're easy. All it takes is a little money?

1019
01:05:18,670 --> 01:05:22,140
That's right. I can be bought. I love money.

1020
01:05:22,880 --> 01:05:24,350
What are you going to do about it?

1021
01:05:41,760 --> 01:05:43,000
But seriously...

1022
01:05:45,700 --> 01:05:49,200
After going through all this,

1023
01:05:52,070 --> 01:05:55,210
I realised you absolutely have to have money.

1024
01:05:59,550 --> 01:06:01,480
It was a real wake-up call.

1025
01:06:02,680 --> 01:06:04,250
What if Mom...

1026
01:06:05,690 --> 01:06:08,360
had been seriously hurt?

1027
01:06:12,090 --> 01:06:13,800
Money's a scary thing, isn't it?

1028
01:06:18,130 --> 01:06:19,430
You're just figuring that out now?

1029
01:06:34,820 --> 01:06:36,020
You know.

1030
01:06:36,950 --> 01:06:38,589
I've started keeping a diary lately.

1031
01:06:38,590 --> 01:06:40,320
With the fountain pen you gave me.

1032
01:06:41,390 --> 01:06:42,490
And guess what?

1033
01:06:42,960 --> 01:06:45,360
You know what I find myself writing the most?

1034
01:06:47,060 --> 01:06:49,130
"Did something with Yeong Rye."

1035
01:06:49,230 --> 01:06:50,700
"It was fun."

1036
01:06:50,900 --> 01:06:53,370
"I laughed so hard. I was happy."

1037
01:06:56,600 --> 01:06:59,410
I was never the kind of person who used words like that.

1038
01:07:00,810 --> 01:07:03,340
But thanks to you, life's gotten a little more fun.

1039
01:07:05,950 --> 01:07:07,250
So, you see...

1040
01:07:09,650 --> 01:07:11,190
That doesn't even compare.

1041
01:07:14,590 --> 01:07:16,930
You're giving me something so much more valuable.

1042
01:07:29,000 --> 01:07:30,810
That was a little...

1043
01:07:33,880 --> 01:07:35,940
cheesy, Seo Jong Hee.

1044
01:07:37,980 --> 01:07:39,080
I know.

1045
01:07:41,220 --> 01:07:43,120
I regretted it the second I said it.

1046
01:08:10,250 --> 01:08:12,610
This is my favourite song.

1047
01:08:19,250 --> 01:08:22,659
- So full of love - So full of love

1048
01:08:22,660 --> 01:08:26,089
- You and I alone - You and I alone

1049
01:08:26,090 --> 01:08:29,729
- Where and as what - Where and as what

1050
01:08:29,730 --> 01:08:33,270
- Shall we meet again - Shall we meet again

1051
01:08:56,690 --> 01:08:58,460
(Yeong Sik's Horse Rides)

1052
01:08:58,930 --> 01:09:01,130
Gosh. This beauty is just gleaming.

1053
01:09:01,730 --> 01:09:04,470
It's much more handsome than the last one.

1054
01:09:04,870 --> 01:09:06,600
This must've cost a fortune.

1055
01:09:07,370 --> 01:09:09,500
Did you really get a paycheck advance for this?

1056
01:09:10,140 --> 01:09:12,770
What's gotten into him? That cheapskate personnel manager.

1057
01:09:12,870 --> 01:09:14,979
- Well...
- Well, Yeong Rye...

1058
01:09:14,980 --> 01:09:16,680
is just that good at her job.

1059
01:09:17,080 --> 01:09:18,779
It'd be a huge loss for them if she went to another company.

1060
01:09:18,780 --> 01:09:20,280
So they're just buttering her up.

1061
01:09:20,380 --> 01:09:22,380
Well, at least he knows a good thing when he sees it.

1062
01:09:23,750 --> 01:09:27,090
I can get right back out there and start working tomorrow. Right?

1063
01:09:27,390 --> 01:09:28,690
- Mom.
- Mom.

1064
01:09:29,090 --> 01:09:31,589
No way. What are you talking about, business?

1065
01:09:31,590 --> 01:09:33,899
You need to rest all this week. You can go out next week.

1066
01:09:33,900 --> 01:09:35,229
Nonsense.

1067
01:09:35,230 --> 01:09:38,100
I'm stir-crazy from not working for a few days.

1068
01:09:38,500 --> 01:09:39,729
I'm perfectly fine.

1069
01:09:39,730 --> 01:09:43,809
What do you mean, "perfectly fine?" You look like you should be in bed.

1070
01:09:43,810 --> 01:09:46,009
Hurry up and go rest. I'll get your bed ready.

1071
01:09:46,010 --> 01:09:47,439
- Come on. Go on.
- Honestly. Don't fuss.

1072
01:09:47,440 --> 01:09:50,249
- Go on. Get inside.
- Hey, you little brat.

1073
01:09:50,250 --> 01:09:52,550
When did you get so strong? Oh, my gosh.

1074
01:09:52,780 --> 01:09:54,480
- I told you I'm fine!
- Get in.

1075
01:10:03,090 --> 01:10:04,760
Yeong Rye told me.

1076
01:10:06,330 --> 01:10:08,600
Thank you. I promise I'll pay you back.

1077
01:10:08,700 --> 01:10:11,130
Please. Don't worry about paying me back.

1078
01:10:11,330 --> 01:10:13,070
You two really are siblings, aren't you?

1079
01:10:16,040 --> 01:10:17,770
It's not like I need the money right away.

1080
01:10:18,670 --> 01:10:21,380
If you really insist on paying it back,

1081
01:10:21,940 --> 01:10:24,050
you can play rock-paper-scissors with Yeong Rye for it.

1082
01:10:26,010 --> 01:10:27,280
I was a step too late.

1083
01:10:42,230 --> 01:10:43,500
Okay. Pencils down!

1084
01:10:44,000 --> 01:10:45,370
Hands on your heads.

1085
01:10:45,570 --> 01:10:47,540
Person in the last row, pass the answer sheets forward.

1086
01:10:48,740 --> 01:10:50,040
The answer...

1087
01:10:53,680 --> 01:10:54,880
Here.

1088
01:10:59,510 --> 01:11:01,620
My bad neck always flares up around exam time.

1089
01:11:01,720 --> 01:11:03,079
Maybe from sleeping with my head on the desk all the time?

1090
01:11:03,080 --> 01:11:04,090
Here?

1091
01:11:04,190 --> 01:11:05,719
- Right there. That's the spot.
- Goodness.

1092
01:11:05,720 --> 01:11:06,919
That's something to be proud of.

1093
01:11:06,920 --> 01:11:08,989
Hey! You're messing up my hair.

1094
01:11:08,990 --> 01:11:11,060
You have no idea how much work I put into this this morning.

1095
01:11:11,360 --> 01:11:12,760
It's so sticky.

1096
01:11:13,330 --> 01:11:14,960
What is this? Did you use mousse?

1097
01:11:15,160 --> 01:11:16,830
- Of course I did.
- Why?

1098
01:11:19,230 --> 01:11:20,699
Because, as I've already announced,

1099
01:11:20,700 --> 01:11:23,340
today is our last big blind date of senior year.

1100
01:11:23,440 --> 01:11:24,469
So you're coming, right?

1101
01:11:24,470 --> 01:11:27,179
I made it very clear I'm not going. You go on your own.

1102
01:11:27,180 --> 01:11:28,280
Come on. Hey.

1103
01:11:28,680 --> 01:11:30,110
Can't you do this one little thing for your friend?

1104
01:11:30,710 --> 01:11:32,650
The numbers are already set!

1105
01:11:33,720 --> 01:11:36,620
My handsome and cool friend, who's also super loyal. Jae Pil.

1106
01:11:37,050 --> 01:11:38,090
Brother!

1107
01:11:38,290 --> 01:11:40,419
So now I'm your brother? You say that when you want a favour.

1108
01:11:40,420 --> 01:11:42,089
- I'm begging you.
- No.

1109
01:11:42,090 --> 01:11:44,059
- Please, just for an hour!
- Let go.

1110
01:11:44,060 --> 01:11:47,060
Please, just for one hour!

1111
01:11:48,060 --> 01:11:50,000
- Gosh.
- I'll owe you big. Just one hour.

1112
01:11:50,870 --> 01:11:53,170
You're driving me nuts. Brother!

1113
01:11:53,300 --> 01:11:55,039
Please.

1114
01:11:55,040 --> 01:11:57,039
So Yeong and Jeong Hui were supposed to go,

1115
01:11:57,040 --> 01:12:00,109
but they bailed when they got tickets for "Music Top Ten."

1116
01:12:00,110 --> 01:12:02,309
You got to help me out, just this once.

1117
01:12:02,310 --> 01:12:04,879
It's a 4-on-4 date. How can only 2 of us show up?

1118
01:12:04,880 --> 01:12:06,879
No way. I hate these things.

1119
01:12:06,880 --> 01:12:09,049
I know, right? It's always a bunch of losers.

1120
01:12:09,050 --> 01:12:10,989
But they said one of them is very popular.

1121
01:12:10,990 --> 01:12:12,389
For real!

1122
01:12:12,390 --> 01:12:15,089
- I told you no.
- You go by yourself then.

1123
01:12:15,090 --> 01:12:16,190
Look...

1124
01:12:16,620 --> 01:12:18,829
I'll give you my MyMy.

1125
01:12:18,830 --> 01:12:20,330
You two can listen to music on it.

1126
01:12:21,260 --> 01:12:23,230
- Please.
- It's a cassette player.

1127
01:12:24,630 --> 01:12:27,270
This kind of deal between friends is not exactly proper.

1128
01:12:28,440 --> 01:12:30,470
How many people bailed on this blind date, you said?

1129
01:12:30,570 --> 01:12:31,809
- Two?
- Two.

1130
01:12:31,810 --> 01:12:33,070
Okay.

1131
01:12:35,940 --> 01:12:37,349
We'll take their spots.

1132
01:12:37,350 --> 01:12:39,749
Seo Jong Hee! What are you talking about?

1133
01:12:39,750 --> 01:12:41,620
We have class.

1134
01:12:53,160 --> 01:12:56,100
A group date? No way.

1135
01:12:56,930 --> 01:12:58,129
No way.

1136
01:12:58,130 --> 01:12:59,629
No way. That's out of the question.

1137
01:12:59,630 --> 01:13:01,370
Why is it out of the question?

1138
01:13:01,470 --> 01:13:03,400
I always wanted to try one of those group dates.

1139
01:13:03,700 --> 01:13:05,269
Let's just do it while we have the chance. Okay?

1140
01:13:05,270 --> 01:13:07,710
Then what about our class?

1141
01:13:08,010 --> 01:13:09,180
And besides...

1142
01:13:10,480 --> 01:13:13,580
I don't feel right about going and pretending to be a day student.

1143
01:13:13,680 --> 01:13:16,050
Why? I think it sounds fun.

1144
01:13:16,550 --> 01:13:18,920
And Ju Gyeong said she could lend us the uniforms.

1145
01:13:19,220 --> 01:13:20,819
Let's do it, Yeong Rye. Please?

1146
01:13:20,820 --> 01:13:23,160
No. I can't do it.

1147
01:13:23,960 --> 01:13:28,330
You know I'm a terrible liar.

1148
01:13:29,160 --> 01:13:30,260
- I can't.
- Hey.

1149
01:13:30,360 --> 01:13:32,200
You only get better at lying with practice.

1150
01:13:32,300 --> 01:13:34,040
Come on. Please?

1151
01:13:35,900 --> 01:13:38,070
Okay, fine.

1152
01:13:38,970 --> 01:13:40,740
Then I'm cashing in that favour right now.

1153
01:13:41,640 --> 01:13:44,780
You know, the wish I've been saving, the one you promised you'd grant?

1154
01:13:45,480 --> 01:13:46,779
You haven't forgotten, have you?

1155
01:13:46,780 --> 01:13:48,420
But that's...

1156
01:14:04,030 --> 01:14:05,470
- Hey.
- What?

1157
01:14:05,670 --> 01:14:06,930
One hour. That's it.

1158
01:14:08,170 --> 01:14:09,739
We're here for one hour, tops. Then I'm off to boxing.

1159
01:14:09,740 --> 01:14:12,570
Fine. Suit yourself.

1160
01:14:12,870 --> 01:14:14,810
You can just sit there and look pretty.

1161
01:14:14,910 --> 01:14:16,580
After all, your only job...

1162
01:14:16,680 --> 01:14:18,910
is to be the eye candy that brings up our average.

1163
01:14:25,120 --> 01:14:26,290
Hey. They're here.

1164
01:15:07,190 --> 01:15:10,030
(A Hundred Memories)

1165
01:15:28,250 --> 01:15:30,119
- I had fun today.
- Bye!

1166
01:15:30,120 --> 01:15:32,450
Hey. They're just leaving like this?

1167
01:15:32,550 --> 01:15:34,319
Are you planning to ask them on another date?

1168
01:15:34,320 --> 01:15:35,359
What?

1169
01:15:35,360 --> 01:15:37,530
I have a great idea.

1170
01:15:37,830 --> 01:15:39,090
What are you up to?

1171
01:15:40,090 --> 01:15:41,359
A boxing gym event?

1172
01:15:41,360 --> 01:15:43,899
They asked me to tell you they really want to invite you.

1173
01:15:43,900 --> 01:15:45,269
The handsome one.

1174
01:15:45,270 --> 01:15:47,070
He is the one who is into Yeong Rye.

1175
01:15:47,270 --> 01:15:48,669
(What's on your mind? Are you thinking of Han Jae Pil?)

1176
01:15:48,670 --> 01:15:50,500
I'm sure it's not like that.

1177
01:15:51,010 --> 01:15:52,470
Are you coming today?

1178
01:15:52,570 --> 01:15:54,179
- Hi.
- Hi.

1179
01:15:54,180 --> 01:15:55,209
Let's go.

1180
01:15:55,210 --> 01:15:56,239
It'll be fun.

1181
01:15:56,240 --> 01:15:57,780
(Giant Boxing Gym)

1182
01:16:05,390 --> 01:16:06,490
Stop it!

1183
01:16:08,860 --> 01:16:10,220
Stop it.
